 AÂ multi-disciplinary approach by the SAPS yielded results when four people were arrested allegedly transporting a large quantity of dagga to Cape Town. According to police information, members of the Dordrecht SAPS, together with members of traffic department, conducted a successful operation comprising of a stop and search and vehicle checkpoint. "While conducting the operation they stopped a Minibus Taxi coming from Ntabankulu to Cape Town," described police spokesperson, W/O Moitheri Bojabotseha. "Upon searching the vehicle with four passengers, when a large quantity of dagga was found wrapped in plastic bags. "All the suspects will appear in Dordrecht District court soon facing charge of dealing in dagga." The Elliot Cluster Commander, Colonel Gezani applauded the swift action by all the members involved. 